dcterms:description: A dataset containing source codes submitted by students for programming tasks, filtered to include only those tasks with more than 350 submissions.
dcterms:title: Common Data Subset

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of programming tasks that are similar in terms of task description and coding implementation, used to evaluate the robustness and effectiveness of the proposed model.
dcterms:title: Similar Task Dataset

dcterms:description: A graph representing the integrated data flow and function call information into the Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) to characterize both syntactic and semantic information from the source codes.
dcterms:title: FDA Graph

dcterms:creator: F. Miller
A. Vandome
J. Mcbrewster
dcterms:description: An intermediate representation of a program generated through the program syntax and semantic analysis, characterizing the grammar structure and execution order of a program.
dcterms:title: AST (Abstract Syntax Tree)

dcterms:creator: X. Liu
Y. Tang
dcterms:description: A graph that models the function semantic information in a program, where each node represents a function and each edge denotes the function-call relation between two functions.
dcterms:title: FCG (Function Call Graph)

dcterms:creator: B. M. Olenick
C. A. Szyperski
D. G. Hunt
G. L. Hughes
W. A. Manis
T. Zmrhal
dcterms:description: A graph that captures the data flow and control flow information associated with the program runtime, characterizing the unique semantic information of a program.
dcterms:title: DFG (Data Flow Graph)

dcterms:description: A dataset containing programming tasks and their corresponding source codes submitted by students, used for program classification.
dcterms:title: Programming Tasks Dataset
